<br>
&quot;if they are not allowed retribution on individuals for voicing unpopular opinions why should we be able to do it in impunity?&quot;<br>
<br>
<br>
Because we (the people) are the conscience of the government, and as a whole are responsible for interpreting the spirit of the law rather than the letter.<br>
<br>
If you think of Free Speech as some intrinsically “pure” ideal, you are naive. Many a silver-tongued monster has hidden behind its mask.<br>
<br>
Free speech is a <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>right</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> empowered by our society’s values….NOT some inalienable dogma. If someone challenges its value through abuse, society reacts as it sees fit.<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
-Morloc<br>
